Below is an instruction that describes a task. Write a response that appropriately completes the request.

### Instruction:
what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Response:

The command you provided is used to establish an SSH connection between two hosts over the network. Specifically, it connects to a remote host named 'user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com' using the specified key file "~/UserKey.pem". The '-C' flag is used to enable compression of data during transmission, while the '-L' flag specifies that a local port (in this case 25900) should be forwarded to a remote port (5900) on the same host. This allows for secure communication between two hosts over the network using SSH protocol.
